			<h2>How to Get Started with AI Automation</h2>

			<h3>Step 1: Identify Your Biggest Time Wasters</h3>
			<p>Where does your team spend the most time on repetitive tasks? Common answers:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Answering the same customer questions over and over</li>
				<li>Manually following up with leads</li>
				<li>Data entry between systems</li>
				<li>Creating reports</li>
				<li>Scheduling appointments</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Step 2: Start with One High-Impact Use Case</h3>
			<p>Don't try to automate everything at once. Pick one process that:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Consumes significant time</li>
				<li>Is highly repetitive and predictable</li>
				<li>Directly impacts revenue or customer satisfaction</li>
			</ul>

			<p><strong>Best First Projects:</strong></p>
			<ul>
				<li>AI receptionist (if you get frequent calls)</li>
				<li>Email automation for lead nurturing</li>
				<li>Automated appointment scheduling</li>
				<li>Customer onboarding workflows</li>
			</ul>

